<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="770" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2804a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Warren</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-07T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 7,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>134. Department’s No. 129, October 30, 4 p.m.</p>
                        <p>If Japanese Government does not object to delay Department would prefer
                            awaiting Stevens’ arrival in Washington before giving final
                            consideration to point 4 of Japanese instructions stated in your No.
                            172, October 17, 2 p.m. If Stevens passes through Tokyo please consult
                            with him on subject acquainting yourself fully with the facts.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>